    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-08-11T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-08-11T04:00:00-05:00" n="467"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d467">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">320/8–1151: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Union of South Africa</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Connelly</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Pretoria</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-08-11T11:00:00+02:00"
                            >August 11, 1951—11 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>46. Cabinet has made decision on South West Africa (<gloss target="#t_reEmbtel1"
                        >reEmbtel</gloss> 38 August 3) <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss>
                    Secy Forsyth told one of my colleagues several days ago. Reply to <hi
                        rend="italic">ad hoc</hi> comite’s July 11 ltr to Jooste now being drafted
                    will: <list>
                        <label>(1)</label>
                        <item>Reiterate Union’s willingness enter agreement with US, UK and France
                            as remaining principal allied and associated powers.</item>
                        <label>(2)</label>
                        <item>Be based on provisions League Nations mandate.</item>
                        <label>(3)</label>
                        <item>Provide for any two of three powers to take a disputed point to <gloss
                                target="#t_ICJ1">ICJ</gloss>.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>Forsyth reported as saying while report’s petitions will not be submitted to any
                        <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> body Union reply will still “leave door
                    open” for further negotiations. Copies Union reply will be given US, UK, France
                    for info.</p>
                <p>While above comes second-hand we have no reason doubt it represents present
                    position. Will check with Forsyth earliest opportunity.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Connelly</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
